# Architecture Review Checklist

Apply this **in addition** to the
[review checklist](/{{DOCS_AGENT_DIR}}/review-checklist.md) whenever a change
touches module boundaries, ownership, public interfaces, concurrency, or the
error-handling strategy.

## Boundaries and dependency direction

- [ ] The change respects the dependency direction declared in `{{CONTRACT_FILE}}`
      (lower-level modules do not import higher-level ones).
- [ ] No new cross-boundary dependency was added without justification.
- [ ] Composition/wiring stays at the intended seam; lower modules remain reusable.

## Ownership and lifetime

- [ ] Every new resource has a clear owner and a defined lifetime.
- [ ] No hidden global/shared mutable state was introduced.

## Concurrency

- [ ] Shared state crossing threads/tasks is synchronized or clearly immutable.
- [ ] Ordering and reentrancy assumptions are documented where they matter.

## Error handling

- [ ] Failure is explicit (typed errors / results), not silent.
- [ ] Invariants are checked at boundaries, not deep in call stacks.

## Reversibility

- [ ] The change can be reverted or evolved later (no premature, hard-to-undo
      abstraction; no one-way door taken without a note in the task/ADR).
